<MudDialog>
    <DialogContent>
		
		<div>
	<ol>
		<li>
			<p align="justify" style="line-height: 108%; margin-bottom: 0.11in">
				<u>
					<b>Introduction</b>
				</u>
			</p>
		</li>
	</ol>
	<p align="justify" style="line-height: 108%; text-indent: 0.5in; margin-bottom: 0.11in">
The purpose of this OVMC is to set out the terms and conditions of OVMC Program. 
</p>
	<ol start="2">
		<li>
			<p align="justify" style="line-height: 108%; margin-bottom: 0.11in">
				<u>
					<b>Definition</b>
				</u>
			</p>
		</li>
	</ol>
	<p align="justify" style="line-height: 108%; text-indent: 0.5in; margin-bottom: 0.11in">
		<b>Oman Post </b>shall mean Oman Post SAOC.</p>
	<p align="justify" style="line-height: 108%; text-indent: 0.5in; margin-bottom: 0.11in">
		<b>OVMC Program</b> shall mean Oman Visa Medical Center .</p>
	<p align="justify" style="line-height: 108%; margin-left: 0.5in; margin-bottom: 0.11in">
		<b>Fee</b> means the fee charged by Oman Post on expatriates for booking vouchers for visa and medical examinations via OVMC’s e-system. 
</p>
	<ol start="3">
		<li>
			<p style="line-height: 108%; margin-bottom: 0.11in">
				<u>
					<b>Scope of Services</b>
				</u>
			</p>
		</li>
	</ol>
	<p style="line-height: 108%; margin-left: 0.5in; margin-bottom: 0.11in">

	</p>
	<p style="line-height: 108%; margin-left: 0.5in; margin-bottom: 0.11in">
Oman Post acts only as an administrative facilitator. 
</p>
	<p align="justify" style="line-height: 108%; margin-left: 0.5in; margin-bottom: 0.11in">
The Website provides an online platform for applicants, employers, authorised recruitment agencies and/or their representatives to
register applicant details, submit preliminary information, obtain queue or token numbers, schedule appointments for medical examination
and/or related visa-processing services, and access status updates where available.</p>
	<p align="justify" style="line-height: 108%; margin-left: 0.5in; margin-bottom: 0.11in">
Oman Post does not provide medical, immigration or visa advice and has no role in medical assessments, medical outcomes, or visa
decision-making. All medical evaluations and visa decisions remain the sole responsibility of the relevant Oman Ministry of Health
appointed and verified medical service provider and/or the relevant Diplomatic Mission/Embassy.</p>

	<p align="justify" style="line-height: 108%; margin-left: 0.5in; margin-bottom: 0.11in">
		<br/>
	</p>
	<ol start="4">
		<li>
			<p style="line-height: 108%; margin-bottom: 0.11in">
				<u>
					<b>Eligibility And Requirements</b>
				</u>
			</p>
		</li>
	</ol>
	<p style="line-height: 108%; text-indent: 0.5in; margin-bottom: 0.11in">
		<b>Service Eligibility</b>. Applicants must be over 18 years old for work visa registrations.</p>
	<p align="justify" style="line-height: 108%; margin-left: 0.5in; margin-bottom: 0.11in">
		<b>Passport Validity</b>. All applicants must hold a passport with a minimum validity of six (6) months prior to its expiry date when they enter Sultanate of Oman.</p>
	<p align="justify" style="line-height: 108%; margin-left: 0.5in; margin-bottom: 0.11in">
		<b>Required Documentation</b>. Applicants must present an original passport and the appointment letter at the Oman Visa and Medical Center.</p>
	<p align="justify" style="line-height: 108%; text-indent: 0.5in; margin-bottom: 0.11in">
		<b>Fee Policy</b>. 
</p>
			<div style="padding: 0 100px;">
	<ol type="a">
		<li>
			<p align="justify" style="line-height: 108%; margin-bottom: 0.11in">
	Oman Post shall amend the Fee from time to time as it deems necessary.</p>
		</li>
		<li>
			<p align="justify" style="line-height: 108%; margin-bottom: 0.11in">
	In any case, the Fee shall be paid in full and in advance through the system and it is non-refundable in nature.</p>
		</li>
		<li>
			<p align="justify" style="line-height: 108%; margin-bottom: 0.11in">
	The Fee shall be due on the submission thereof, irrespective of the	application outcome. 
	</p>
		</li>
	</ol>
	</div>
	<p align="justify" style="line-height: 108%; margin-left: 0.5in; margin-bottom: 0.11in">
		<b>Compliance with Laws</b>. Applicants are legally required to comply with all applicable laws in the Sultanate of Oman, as well the country they are applying from; failure to do so may lead to legal inquiry.</p>
	<p align="justify" style="line-height: 108%; margin-left: 0.5in; margin-bottom: 0.11in">
		<b>Right of Rejection</b>. The Sultanate of Oman reserves the absolute right to approve or deny any visa application at its sole discretion, without the obligation to provide justification for such decisions.</p>
	<p align="justify" style="line-height: 108%; margin-left: 0.5in; margin-bottom: 0.11in">
		<b>Data Accuracy</b>. By submitting an application, the user confirms all provided information is true and accurate; Oman Post is not
liable for errors in user-submitted profiles. The applicant is solely responsible for ensuring that all information submitted through the
Website is true, accurate, complete and consistent with the applicant’s passport, employment documents, visa application
documents and any other supporting documents. Oman Post shall not be liable for any rejection, delay, cancellation, rescheduling, medical
report issue, visa refusal or other consequence arising from incorrect, incomplete, inconsistent or outdated information submitted
by the applicant or on the applicant’s behalf.</p>
	<p align="justify" style="line-height: 108%; margin-left: 0.5in; margin-bottom: 0.11in">
		<b>Appointment, Queue and Scheduling</b>. Appointment dates, time slots and queue numbers are subject to availability and may be
allocated automatically or manually based on the applicable process, capacity of the relevant centre, system availability and operational
requirements. Oman Post reserves the right to reschedule, cancel, suspend or modify any appointment due to system issues, public
holidays, force majeure events, medical centre requirements, government instructions, technical interruptions or other
circumstances beyond its reasonable control.</p>
	<p align="justify" style="line-height: 108%; margin-left: 0.5in; margin-bottom: 0.11in">
		<b>Attendance at Medical Centre. </b>The applicant must attend the designated medical centre or visa/medical examination centre on the
scheduled date and time, together with the original passport, appointment confirmation, payment receipt and any other documents
required by the relevant authority or medical centre. Late attendance, non-attendance, incomplete documents, mismatch of
information, or failure to comply with medical centre instructions may result in refusal of service, cancellation of the appointment,
additional fees or requirement to book a new appointment.</p>
	<p style="line-height: 108%; margin-bottom: 0.11in">
		<b>General terms
and conditions. </b>
	</p>
	<p align="justify" style="line-height: 108%; margin-left: 0.5in; margin-bottom: 0.11in">
These Terms and Conditions apply solely to visa applicants/users accessing and using the Oman Post website. These Terms do not create
or govern any contractual relationship between Oman Post and any Diplomatic Mission/Embassy or any third-party service provider
(including any medical service provider).</p>
	<p align="justify" style="line-height: 108%; margin-left: 0.5in; margin-bottom: 0.11in">
