	can be used to identify an individual, such as name, sex, date of
	birth, nationality, race, religion, dialect group, personal
	identification numbers, biometrics (fingerprints, facial image and
	iris image) including photograph-of-the-day (captured for facial
	authentication when an individual performs immigration clearance at
	our checkpoints) and photograph on the passport biodata page;</span>
			</p>
		</li>
		<li>
			<p align="justify" style="line-height: 108%; margin-bottom: 0.11in">
				<span lang="en-US">
					<b>Travel Document information</b>
				</span>
				<span lang="en-US">&nbsp;such
	as travel document number, travel document type, country of issue,
	date of issue, date of expiry, including supporting documents with
	information such as photocopy of the passport biodata page;</span>
			</p>
		</li>
		<li>
			<p style="line-height: 108%; margin-bottom: 0.11in">
				<span lang="en-US">
					<b>Contact
	information</b>
				</span>
				<span lang="en-US">&nbsp;such as residential
	address, phone number, email address;</span>
			</p>
		</li>
		<li>
			<p align="justify" style="line-height: 108%; margin-bottom: 0.11in">
				<span lang="en-US">
					<b>Transaction information</b>
				</span>
